// Omni Language Specification: Ownership Keywords
//
// The keywords `own` and `shared` are recognized by the parser but currently
// have NO runtime effect. They are syntactic placeholders for future ownership
// semantics (similar to Rust's ownership model).
//
// Current status (v1):
//   - `own` in return position (e.g., `fn foo() -> own Self`) is parsed and
//     silently ignored by codegen. The OVM treats it as a no-op.
//   - `shared` is not used in the stdlib currently.
//
// Future (post-v1, when trait system is stable):
//   - `own T` will mean exclusive ownership (like Rust's owned values)
//   - `shared T` will mean shared/immutable reference (like Arc<T>)
//   - Move semantics and borrow checking will be enforced
//
// Until then, these keywords serve as documentation only.
